# Environment Variables Setup

Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in your values:

```bash
cp env.template .env.local
```

## Required Variables

```env
# Google OAuth Client ID
# Get from: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_google_client_id.apps.googleusercontent.com

# Redirect URL (must match Google OAuth settings)
NEXT_PUBLIC_REDIRECT_URL=http://localhost:3000

# OAuth URL
NEXT_PUBLIC_OAUTH_URL=https://accounts.google.com/o/oauth2/v2/auth

# Enoki API Key
# Get from: https://enoki.mystenlabs.com/
NEXT_PUBLIC_ENOKI_API_KEY=enoki_public_...

# Enoki Endpoints (Testnet)
NEXT_PUBLIC_ENOKI_NONCE_URL=https://api.enoki.mystenlabs.com/v1/zklogin/nonce
NEXT_PUBLIC_ENOKI_ZKP_URL=https://api.enoki.mystenlabs.com/v1/zklogin/zkp
```

## Setup Instructions

1. **Google OAuth Setup:**
   - Go to [Google Cloud Console](https://console.cloud.google.com/)
   - Create a new project or select existing
   - Enable Google+ API
   - Create OAuth 2.0 credentials
   - Add authorized redirect URI: `http://localhost:3000`
   - Copy the Client ID

2. **Enoki API Key:**
   - Visit [Enoki Dashboard](https://enoki.mystenlabs.com/)
   - Create an account
   - Generate an API key for Testnet
   - Copy the public API key
